FuncDef: The display nat session-table size command displays information about session table resources assigned to service boards.

ParaDef.Info:
Specifies the slot ID of a service board.
The value is a string of 1 to 15 case-sensitive characters, spaces not supported.

ExtraInfo:
Usage Scenario
To view information about session table resources assigned to service boards, run the display nat session-table size command.
Precautions
This command is supported only on the admin VS.
This command is applicable only to the VSUF-80/VSUF-160/VSUI-160-E/VSUI-400/VSUI-400-E/VSUI-400A/VSUI-400A-E/VSUI-400-S/VSUI-400A-S.
